Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @Potatoes{700%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop 
them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, sprinkle over 
@Cajun Spice Mix{1/2%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), then 
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}. 
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve the @Bell Pepper{1}(halved and sliced into thin strips) and 
discard the core and seeds. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and 
grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @Diced Chorizo{90%grams} and sliced pepper and fry, stirring, 
until the pepper is slightly charred, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Once the pepper is charred, stir in the garlic, @Tomato Puree{30%grams} and 
remaining @Cajun Spice Mix{1/2%sachet} to the pan. Fry for ~{1%minute}. 
Season with salt and pepper.

Drain the @Sweetcorn{150%grams} in a #sieve{}, then add to the pan.

Stir in the @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%grams}, @Tomato Ketchup{1%tbsp} and 
@Water{100%ml} for the sauce. Bring to the boil, then simmer until thickened, 
~{8-10%minutes}.

While the sauce simmers, zest and halve the @Lime{1}. Grate the 
@Mature Cheddar Cheese{40%grams}.

In a small #bowl{}, mix together the @Soured Cream{75%grams} and lime zest. 
Set aside.

Halve the @Avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the 
flesh out onto a board and chop into 1cm chunks.

Pop the avocado chunks into another small bowl. Squeeze in some lime juice and 
season with salt and pepper. Stir to combine, then set aside.

When your sauce has thickened, remove the pan from the heat.

Squeeze in the remaining lime juice and stir to combine. Taste the sauce and 
add more salt and pepper if needed.

Share the wedges between your #plates{}, then top with the corn and pepper 
mixture.

Spoon over the avocado and top with dollops of the zesty soured cream.

Sprinkle over the grated cheese to finish.

Enjoy!